85 milligrams of folic acid, within an acceptable industry
86 standard deviation of error.
87 (b) This section shall not apply to either of the
88 following:
89 (1) Corn masa flour or corn masa products made by or
90 supplied to a cottage food production operation.
91 (2) Corn Certified organic corn masa flour or corn masa
92 products offered for sale by a grocery store offering
93 conforming products.
94 (c) This section shall not apply to snack foods. For
95 the purposes of this section, "snack food" means a food
96 product that is intended for immediate consumption, is
97 typically prepackaged in small or single-serving portions, and
98 is primarily consumed between meals, including, but not
99 limited to, chips, crisps, or extruded food products. The term
100 does not include a food product primarily made from corn masa
101 flour or wet corn masa products that is bulk packaged or is
102 commonly used as a primary ingredient in meal preparation,
103 including, but not limited to, tortillas.
104 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
105 1, 2026.
